There are 5 types of units

    Absolute length --> fixed number of no
    Example:     PX--> pixels , inxhes , cms

    Relative length unit --> Based on the font size of the parent
    Example: 10% , em , rem (root element --> parent)

    Viewport Percentage Lengths --> Height and width of the screen
    Example: 100vh and 100vw


Color:
        Named color --> red, green, black etc
        Hexadeciaml Component --> RGB or RRGGBB components [red , green , blue] (#rrggbb)
        Alpha--> RGBA
        HSL --> Hue , saturation , lightness, Alpha mainly used by the designers

Color Gradient:

    Raidal Gradient: starts from center and expand
        Example: background: Radial gradient(to right, color);

    Linear Gradient: starts from left to right 
        Example: background: Linear gradient(circle/elipse etc, color);

